</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Function: consistent_configuration_type 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.consistent_configuration_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.consistent_configuration_type">
The <b>consistent_configuration_type</b> function validates if the type of a <b>Configuration</b> instance is consistent with the type of the associated <b>Class_condition_association</b> or <b>Class_specification_association</b> instance.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.consistent_configuration_type.config">
The <b>Configuration</b> instance whose type is validated in relation to the type of the <b>Class_category_association</b> or <b>Class_specification_association</b> instance associated.
</ext_description>
